<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1410,1507]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
This genus includes the green mantispids which are commonly found in the Americas, it consisting of three species widely distributed from the eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[559,710,1446,1471]" name="United States of America" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">United States</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[749,861,1446,1471]" name="Argentina" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Argentina</collectingCountry>
including 
<collectingCountry box="[984,1043,1446,1471]" name="Cuba" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[1059,1231,1446,1471]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman 
<number box="[1170,1231,1447,1471]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In this paper we registered all the three species: 
<taxonomicName box="[503,658,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Zeugomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compellens">
<emphasis box="[503,658,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Z. compellens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[672,780,1484,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Zeugomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[672,780,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Z. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[841,974,1484,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Zeugomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis box="[841,974,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Z. virescens</emphasis>
